<div class="answer_expl">
<div class="expl_content">
<p>In particular, a retinoid drug called isotretinoin can delay healing and cause scarring. You must wait one year after using retinoids before you get a chemical peel or dermabrasion.</p>
<p>Your dermatologist will need to take a complete medical history to be sure you get the best results.</p>
